title: Britney Spears - Blackout
description:
Britney Jean Spears [born December 2nd 1981 in Kentwood, Louisiana ] is an American pop music singer, songwriter, dancer, actress and author. Her debut album &#039;Baby One More Time&#039;, released in January 1999, propelled her to international stardom. It spawned its five singles, including &#039;Baby One More Time&#039;, which topped the Billboard Hot 100. She released her second studio album &#039;Oops! I Did It Again&#039; in 2000 with similar success. Her third album &#039;Britney&#039; was released in November 2001, followed by the release of her fourth album &#039;In The Zone&#039; in November 2003. The album&#039;s single &#039;Toxic&#039; was an international success and has won Spears her first ever Grammy Award. The collection &#039;Greatest Hits: My Prerogative&#039; was released in November 2004 followed by a brief career break.

&#039;Blackout&#039; is the fifth studio album by American pop singer Britney Spears. It is scheduled for release on October 29th 2007 in the UK and October 30th 2007 in the U.S.A., Canada and New Zealand. It is her first studio album of new material since &#039;In The Zone&#039; in 2003. &#039;Gimme More&#039; is a song written by James Washington, Keri Hilson, Marcella Araica and Nate Hills and produced by Danja, it is the first single from the album and Spears&#039;s highest peaking single in the United States since &#039;Baby One More Time&#039;, having reached number three on the Billboard Hot 100.
